snippet.textDisplay: Brother Humza, I write this to you with a tear rolling down my face. I cried throughout this video, it was very well made. You will not remember me, but we have actually met once. It was at the Manchester mela in 2012. Brother Yogesh Kalia and yourself took a picture with me. Also Brother JP filmed the event there. I pray to Allah to find a wife like Sara. I am recently and this pulled at my heart strings. The video accurately depicted how our faith can go up and down depending on our situation. This life is indeed a test brother Humza. Your video showed this beautifully. I have been a fan of yours from day one. I always knew your intention was pure, despite the controversy you went through with the ummah. I never really leave messages. But I felt compelled to do so on this video as it made me cry so much. Remember not all people are like him. All people, Muslim or non Muslim have the same life force breathed into them from Allah. Hence why we respect everybody. There is a saying in Christianity, we are all children of God or made in the image of God. What they mean by this is I think is that our life force is from Allah. Without this we are just dirt, the earth, which we will return to when our body dies. But our life force from Allah is eternal. Brother Humza, if you have read this message jazakhallah khair, if you miss this message than alhumdillah as it was Allah's will for you not to see this. I will always be your fan, as I know your intention is pure. In Islam that matters most. From Brother Haroon in Manchester. Asslamu alaikum wa rah mutlah he wa barakatuhu.
